I agree, Larry! (and I am a psychic, lol)

I did not watch the show becaus=
e my group and I were actually out investigating  something last night. As =
it is we are very busy with cases, box research and other research and proj=
ects. We do not, therefore, have time to watch other people,often pathetic =
wanna-be famous para-celebs, pretend to be what we really are.



I wrote =
a blog about this whole thing - in this field, thos that can do..those that=
 can&#39;t sit and watch others pretend to do ti on TV.



Laurie
-----Origina=
l Message-----
From: &quot;Larry Weinreich&quot; &lt;LWEINREICH@...&gt;
Sent: Satur=
day, February 14, 2009 1:35pm
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: Re: [EVP=
-ITC] Door To The Dead






I find most paranormal shows have become BS an=
d I don&#39;t watch any. Its all the same &quot;dog and pony&quot; act. Since &quot;Ghost Hunt=
ers&quot; has become a hit &quot;everyone&quot; wants their own tv show or radio show. Its=
 all &quot;look at me&quot;.

                 Sorry I&#39;m very jaded on tv paranormal =
investigators,mediums and evangelists on Sunday mornings. In my book they a=
ll rank just a bit above lawyers but still below pro wrestling.

  (Hows th=
at for an introduction?  :)  )

                  Larry




----- Original=
 Message ----- 

From: [mailto:phenom_investigator@...] John S 

To: =
[mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com 

Sent: Saturday, =
February 14, 2009 9:44 AM

Subject: [EVP-ITC] Door To The Dead












=
I have to admit that I thought I had seen the worst &#39;paranormal&#39; show on te=
levision already. I was wrong. Door to the Dead has exceeded my worst expec=
tations.



Generally, I respect John Oliver&#39;s work as a medium. While I h=
ave no personal experience with him, in the past he has looked and acted mo=
re genuine than not, the rolling of the eyes put aside for the moment.



=
I do take exception to the characterization of the talking box as an Edison=
 device. I have documented the history of Edison, ITC and EVP  [http://www.=
sdparanormal.com/EdisonWhitePaper.html] elsewhere. This is however the smal=
lest concern I have with this show.



Prior to wathcing I had just had a =
conversation with a respected colleague on the West coast regarding interes=
ting phenomena he and others are constantly observing in sites with phenome=
na similar to that on Door to the Dead. None of those measurements were mad=
e by this team. The use of thermal in this situation is not indicated as we=
ll.



The real concern is that no attempt was made to help this family in=
 a broader context. The skeptic did and said nothing skeptical as far as I =
could tell. Key questions were not asked (at least on-camera) that would re=
veal the psycho-dynamics of this family. We know fairly well at this time t=
hat PK phenomena is often centered on a focal person who can exhibit specif=
ic characteristics. That the team seems unaware of this is quite disturbing=
 to a person like myself.



A real research opportunity was lost in this =
case, as was an opportunity to educate the public on the right way to appro=
ach such situations. Continually sending the messages that phenomena is bas=
ed on &#39;demons&#39; and &#39;spirits&#39; exclusively does nothing to further the positi=
on of serious investigators, which is perhaps most troubling of all.







